comment:
* An optional addition to the PIDF Presence Tuple containing service capabilities, which is
     * defined in the servcaps element. See RFC5196, section 3.2.1.

variables.name: DUPLEX_MODE_FULL
variables.comment: The service can simultaneously send and receive data.

variables.name: DUPLEX_MODE_HALF
variables.comment: The service can alternate between sending and receiving data.

variables.name: DUPLEX_MODE_RECEIVE_ONLY
variables.comment: The service can only receive data.

variables.name: DUPLEX_MODE_SEND_ONLY
variables.comment: The service can only send data.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel out, int flags)
public boolean isAudioCapable()
methods.comment:
* Query the audio capable.
         * @return true if the audio is capable, false otherwise.

methods.name: public boolean isVideoCapable()
methods.comment:
* Query the video capable.
         * @return true if the video is capable, false otherwise.

methods.name: public List<String> getSupportedDuplexModes()
methods.comment:
* Get the supported duplex mode list.
         * @return The list of supported duplex mode

methods.name: public List<String> getUnsupportedDuplexModes()
methods.comment:
* Get the unsupported duplex mode list.
         * @return The list of unsupported duplex mode
